main event: A sighting of one star-shaped object, size of a basketball held at arm's length, color blue-green, observed for three hours and five minutes in Watertown, Wisconsin.
interesting points: The object was noted to have a wavering and hovering course,It was sighted in a low western direction,Comments suggest that this sighting was likely attributed to the planet Jupiter,The object was reported by a civilian source,Observation lasted from 4:32 AM on 28th June 1956.
